stylometry: Logical upper limit is when a non linear problem transforms into a linear (integer) problem.  Logical upper limit uses 1,0.  1 means its good to use, and 0 means its not good to use, 0 is a no.  For an example my group did a homework problem that used logical upper limit.  I believe we had 4 machines and 5 workers and we had to figure out what workers would be the most efficient on what machine throughout the week.  So with logical upper limit if the worker was the most efficient on a machine he had a 1 and if was not he had a 0.
